1
00:00:38,820 --> 00:00:40,040
=Visage and Soul=

2
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:43,040
(The "Different Her"
Trilogy on Women's Relationships)

3
00:00:44,720 --> 00:00:47,640
=Episode 8=

4
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:02,320
(Ji Ran,)

5
00:01:02,680 --> 00:01:04,520
(Logic tells me you're gone.)

6
00:01:05,560 --> 00:01:07,680
(But why does this so-called Qin Yu)

7
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:09,720
(have the exact same face as you?)

8
00:01:38,440 --> 00:01:39,880
Xiaomi, you're back!

9
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:42,040
Zhiwei and I were just
talking about you.

10
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:46,800
I came to apologize.

11
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:48,280
That day,

12
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:51,600
I shouldn't have brought up
those painful memories.

13
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:53,280
Zhiwei's right.

14
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,920
We should all move on.

15
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:56,040
But some people

16
00:01:56,880 --> 00:01:59,040
just can't let go of the past.

17
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:04,960
You said we're friends, right?

18
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:05,840
Of course.

19
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:07,040
You remembered?

20
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:08,000
That's great!

21
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:13,960
Then do you know Qin Yu?

22
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:15,280
Qin Yu?

23
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,480
Of course I do.

24
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:19,000
You two were head over heels.

25
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:21,360
But honestly,

26
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:22,960
he really is handsome.

27
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:25,200
Half the girls at school liked him.

28
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:27,040
As for the other half,

29
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:30,040
they were into Zhiwei.

30
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:36,120
Do you even know what handsome means?

31
00:02:52,760 --> 00:02:53,880
Look at these brushstrokes.

32
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:55,760
It's copying the style
of early abstract expressionism.

33
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,840
But the colors are far too commercial.

34
00:02:58,160 --> 00:02:59,480
And while the composition
looks bold,

35
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:00,320
it's actually quite conservative.

36
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:03,360
Now look at this one.

37
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:05,360
Technically flawless.

38
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:06,520
The ultimate academic style.

39
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:08,360
But where's the soul?
Where's the emotion?

40
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,520
There's nothing there.

41
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:10,640
A piece like this

42
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:11,560
has commercial value,

43
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:12,560
but no artistic value.

44
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,280
Are you even listening?

45
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:19,680
I didn't come here
for an art appreciation class.

46
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:20,440
For this exhibition,

47
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:21,800
as long as the paintings sell,
that's all that matters.

48
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:25,520
Qiao Xiaomi.

49
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:29,920
So you're running this gallery

50
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:31,680
just to sell paintings?

51
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:37,560
A commercial gallery

52
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:39,000
is a business after all.

53
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:46,560
Is that what you were after

54
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:47,800
when you first picked up a brush?

55
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:53,840
If you want to paint again,

56
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:55,440
you need passion.

57
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:57,200
You need to truly love it
from the bottom of your heart.

58
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:08,080
Just like loving someone.

59
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:11,600
Just knowing who they are isn't enough.

60
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,720
You have to feel it again.

61
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:16,160
Fall in love again

62
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:18,520
with that first heartbeat.

63
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:32,240
Right now,

64
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:33,760
I just want to cut loose for once.

65
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:36,360
After that,

66
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:38,280
we can talk about

67
00:04:38,280 --> 00:04:39,520
love and all that.

68
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:47,960
Keep up, fiancé.

69
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:05,000
So this is what you meant

70
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:05,920
by "cutting loose"?

71
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:07,360
What else

72
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:08,880
did you think it meant?

73
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:11,560
Fine.

74
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:13,120
Then this time,

75
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:15,360
I'll cut loose with you.

76
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:17,120
But after that,

77
00:05:17,520 --> 00:05:18,400
once we're done,

78
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:21,840
you'll follow my training plan.

79
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,400
Get back to painting.

80
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:25,720
Otherwise, I'll have reason to think

81
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:27,920
you're just dragging this out

82
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:29,960
until the two months are over.

83
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:32,360
You think I'm a sore loser?

84
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,400
A bet's a bet.

85
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:47,560
I just let my guard down earlier.

86
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:49,440
But from now on,

87
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,960
I'm getting serious.

88
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:56,280
You'd better do the same.

89
00:05:56,280 --> 00:05:57,800
Give it everything you've got.

90
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:10,680
Hey.

91
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:11,840
Easy there.

92
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:13,440
You're a grown man.
Is this really necessary?

93
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:15,560
Don't touch it.

94
00:06:23,640 --> 00:06:24,400
Xiaomi,

95
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:27,240
I admit that since I came back,

96
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:29,800
sometimes you feel like a stranger.

97
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:33,800
So much so that
it's like I don't know you at all.

98
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,320
But other times,

99
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:39,080
you feel so familiar.

100
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:41,040
So familiar that

101
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:43,560
it's like you've never changed.

102
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:50,160
Then in your memory,

103
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:52,200
what was I like?

104
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:55,800
Very pretty.

105
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:57,600
How shallow.

106
00:06:58,720 --> 00:07:00,560
So how did you
end up falling for me?

107
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:04,280
Love

108
00:07:05,080 --> 00:07:06,360
doesn't exactly follow logic.

109
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:11,160
You always say
we were deeply in love.

110
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:13,480
But you've never told me

111
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:15,600
how we got together.

112
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:20,720
That year,

113
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:23,400
at the city youth art competition,

114
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,360
you won second place.

115
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,320
Who got first?

116
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,320
Alright, stop.
Don't tell me.

117
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,040
Then what happened?

118
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:35,320
Then we ran into each other
on the street.

119
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:37,320
You picked up my sketchbook.

120
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:38,960
Then you asked me
to an art exhibition.

121
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:42,120
And then?

122
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,880
Then we got together.

123
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:50,720
You're lying.

124
00:07:51,440 --> 00:07:52,400
What am I lying about?

125
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:54,080
I asked you out
to the exhibition?

126
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:55,040
That's right.

127
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:58,840
I...

128
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,960
I asked you out
to the exhibition.

129
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:05,800
Now that sounds believable.

130
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:14,200
Exactly.

131
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:18,960
She confessed to me.

132
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:20,800
And then?

133
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:21,760
How far did it go?

134
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:28,160
We kissed.

135
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,560
Who made the first move?

136
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:35,040
She did.

137
00:08:39,160 --> 00:08:41,880
But honestly,
I still can't shake this feeling.

138
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:44,960
I'm afraid

139
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:46,960
that if she finds out I lied,

140
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,120
she'll hate me.

141
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:53,240
She likes you.

142
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:55,480
Whether you can paint or not,
she likes you.

143
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,360
Be a little more confident.

144
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,920
Girls like confident guys.

145
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:02,800
My dad bought me some new clothes.

146
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:03,840
I'll bring them to you tomorrow.

147
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:05,160
Really?

148
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:08,480
Like this.

149
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:10,120
Take this

150
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:11,960
and twist it into a loop.

151
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:19,480
Qin Yu, can you focus?

152
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:25,320
This hairstyle...

153
00:09:27,560 --> 00:09:28,680
My arm...

154
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:29,960
Alright.

155
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:31,240
Hurry up.

156
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:33,920
Wait.

157
00:09:34,560 --> 00:09:36,800
You dragged me out this late
just to do this?

158
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:40,240
How about

159
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,760
we do something more meaningful?

160
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:45,560
Less talking.

161
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,680
Just do it.

162
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:51,200
We're running out of time.

163
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:53,200
Running out of time for what?

164
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,400
Hurry up.

165
00:10:10,923 --> 00:10:16,843
♪The bud is tinted into wisdom♪

166
00:10:17,323 --> 00:10:20,740
♪Raising butterflies♪

167
00:10:21,693 --> 00:10:23,793
♪Strong and radiant♪

168
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:29,833
♪Adorning the lilies♪

169
00:10:29,843 --> 00:10:33,500
♪Weaving together clouds and poetry♪

170
00:10:34,136 --> 00:10:40,780
♪Circling at the edge of sunset♪

171
00:10:42,203 --> 00:10:48,096
♪Tears are distilled into piles of sand♪

172
00:10:48,746 --> 00:10:51,753
♪The clouds gather fresh water♪

173
00:10:52,270 --> 00:10:55,036
♪For another spring♪

174
00:10:57,423 --> 00:11:04,600
♪My rose blooms high and far away♪

175
00:11:05,173 --> 00:11:11,456
♪Yet it weeps beside my ear♪

176
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:16,600
Happy Birthday to You.

177
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:20,960
Happy Birthday to You.

178
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:22,680
My birthday?

179
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:25,960
Surprised?

180
00:11:26,176 --> 00:11:30,960
♪Tempering my cold eyes,
scorching my back♪

181
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:34,660
♪Cast into the ashes,
evolving into islands♪

182
00:11:34,660 --> 00:11:37,876
♪In the end, I become
the one who can weave♪

183
00:11:38,723 --> 00:11:41,570
♪Rivers that wind around♪

184
00:11:41,950 --> 00:11:44,400
♪Watering these vines
to the ends of the earth♪

185
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:46,200
Don't tell me you're crying.

186
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:49,616
♪I am so heavy, yet so rich♪

187
00:11:49,616 --> 00:11:52,840
♪Great disasters, ordinary joys♪

188
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:54,560
You're really crying?

189
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:55,280
No.

190
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:58,120
It's the candle smoke.

191
00:11:58,120 --> 00:12:00,030
♪In exchange for♪

192
00:12:00,030 --> 00:12:02,360
♪The richness of my soil♪

193
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:03,080
It's just...

194
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:05,600
it's been so long

195
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:07,200
since anyone celebrated my birthday.

196
00:12:09,040 --> 00:12:10,800
Didn't I ever celebrate
your birthday before?

197
00:12:12,936 --> 00:12:19,436
♪Yet it weeps beside my ear♪

198
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:24,170
♪Come walk along my secret path,
my diamond-like heart♪

199
00:12:24,170 --> 00:12:28,156
♪From the ruins rise dazzling thorns♪

200
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:29,840
Thank you.

201
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:31,200
♪The footprints of angels and beasts♪

202
00:12:31,946 --> 00:12:35,340
♪They are all a part of me♪

203
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:37,000
You're welcome.

204
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:39,016
♪Watering these vines
to the ends of the earth♪

205
00:12:39,016 --> 00:12:42,486
♪I am so heavy, yet so rich♪

206
00:12:43,060 --> 00:12:46,616
♪Great disasters, ordinary joys♪

207
00:12:46,616 --> 00:12:50,083
♪Let them drift away with the wind♪

208
00:12:50,083 --> 00:12:55,826
♪In exchange for
the richness of my soil♪

209
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:13,566
♪We say good morning,
we say good night♪

210
00:13:13,570 --> 00:13:17,136
♪We say we miss each other,
but never speak of the hurt♪

211
00:13:18,836 --> 00:13:20,683
♪The sweeter it is,
the luckier we seem♪

212
00:13:20,683 --> 00:13:24,700
♪Yet the more romantic,
the rougher the road♪

213
00:13:25,846 --> 00:13:27,500
♪Let me go, set me free♪

214
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:31,946
♪Let me drown in reckless silence♪

215
00:13:32,330 --> 00:13:37,740
♪We were perfect for each other,
yet you never admitted it♪

216
00:13:39,126 --> 00:13:41,210
♪The freedom you gave me♪

217
00:13:41,210 --> 00:13:44,756
♪Became the heaviest chain I bear♪

218
00:13:46,116 --> 00:13:48,283
♪Love can barely move forward♪

219
00:13:48,283 --> 00:13:52,320
♪Yet the words still linger unspoken♪

220
00:13:53,176 --> 00:13:55,163
♪The closeness I long for♪

221
00:13:55,430 --> 00:14:00,020
♪There's no need for you
to keep avoiding it♪

222
00:14:00,020 --> 00:14:02,110
♪I don't want to break free♪

223
00:14:02,110 --> 00:14:07,336
♪Take back the chains
disguised as freedom♪

